rComments: Mme Frappier is my favourite prof at the university. She always explains things really thoroughly and it's very obvious that she cares about her students. I always enjoyed my classes with her and I'm sad that this was my last one. I highly recommend this prof, especially if you choose to do the independent research course. She's a true gem.

Mme Frappier is a great prof. I had her for Theatre History I. She's pretty much always available outside of class to help students with assignments. Her lecture slides are pretty thorough and she explains things really well. There are a lot of readings to do (nearly every class) and the textbook for this class is really dry, but also optional.

I've had Loulou for my whole bachelor's degree -- she's a tough grader, but is absolutely a gem to the department. She will push you beyond your limits and sees potential in each and every student. I wish she wouldn't teach THE1700 as she is overqualified for intro classes! I have truly appreciated her input in her independant study class.
She's nice but unclear, she takes alot of points off for grammar.
She's an absolute sweetheart who will try her best to make you succeed. She will do everything in her power to keep you interested in something she is clearly VERY PASSIONATE about.

I will preface this by saying I almost failed her class, but through my own fault.  Louise Frappier is a complete sweetheart.  Her class is tough, no lie, but she's fair and she is very willing to help.  She genuinely gives a damn.
